    },
    {
      "name": "Ginger",
      "amount": "1 inch",
      "notes": "grated"
    },
    {
      "name": "Ssam wrap",
      "amount": "4-6 leaves"
    }
  ],
  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the claypot over medium heat.",
    "In a bowl, whisk together sesame oil, gochujang, soy sauce, and rice vinegar.",
    "Add the sliced sweet potatoes to the bowl and toss to coat with the sauce.",
    "Add the minced garlic and grated ginger to the bowl and toss to combine.",
    "Add the sweet potato mixture to the preheated claypot and cook for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.",
    "While the sweet potatoes are cooking, prepare the ssam wrap by rinsing the leaves in cold water and patting them dry.",
    "To assemble the wrap, place a few slices of the cooked sweet potato onto a ssam leaf and serve.",
    "Repeat with the remaining ingredients.",
    "Serve immediately and enjoy."
  ],
